To include iframe content in a PDF generated from HTML using iText, you need to:

1. Use a library like JSoup to download the iframe content as HTML.

2. Insert the downloaded iframe HTML into the main HTML at the iframe location.

3. Pass the combined HTML to iText for rendering.

Here is an example code snippet:

```java
// HTML containing iframe 
String html = "<html><body>...</body><iframe src='iframe.html' /></html>";

// Parse HTML 
Document doc = Jsoup.parse(html);

// Get iframe src 
String iframeSrc = doc.select("iframe").first().attr("src");

// Download iframe HTML
String iframeHtml = Jsoup.connect(iframeSrc).get().html();

// Insert iframe HTML into main html
doc.select("iframe").first().html(iframeHtml);

// Render combined html to pdf
ITextRenderer renderer = new ITextRenderer();
renderer.setDocumentFromString(doc.html());
renderer.layout(); 
renderer.createPDF(pdfDoc); 
```

The key steps are:

1. Use JSoup to parse original HTML and find iframe src
2. Download iframe HTML using JSoup 
3. Insert downloaded iframe HTML into main HTML
4. Pass combined HTML to iTextRenderer

This will include the iframe content by downloading it and integrating it into the main HTML before PDF conversion.

Some caveats:

- May not work for all iframe content
- Additional CSS/script handling may be needed
- Inline frames and cross-domain restrictions can complicate it

But for basic iframe content, this approach can allow you to include it in the generated PDF.

